FBIS3-23450 "jptot013__l94131" JPRS-TOT-94-013-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 21 March 1994 WEST EUROPE ITALY Disgruntled Criminal Hijacks Plane at Rome Airport 160 People Held AU2103114294 Paris AFP in English 1136 GMT 21 Mar 94 AU2103114294 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Rome, March 21 (AFP) -- A Sicilian was holding 160 people hostage aboard a plane that landed at Fiumicino airport here at 11:30 a.m. (1030 GMT) from Palermo, airport officials said. The hostages were 154 passengers and six crew. The hijacker, who has not been identified further, has asked to speak with the airport director. The hijacker was said to be from Trapani in western Sicily, with a criminal record and psychological problems. The plane was from the domestic Italian company Meridiana and has been isolated on a runway.
